Text: Abu Dhabi adalah destinasi terakhir saya dalam rangka lawatan rasmi di Asia Barat. Ketika di Abu Dhabi dari 10-11 Mac 2021, saya telah diterima menghadap YM Putera Mahkota Abu Dhabi yang juga  Timbalan Komander Tertinggi Angkatan Tentera UAE, Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan.
Translated Text: Abu Dhabi is my last destination in the framework of an official visit in West Asia. While in Abu Dhabi from 10-11 March 2021, I was received before His Highness the Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi who is also the Deputy Supreme Commander of the UAE Armed Forces, Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan.

Text: Saya turut diterima menghadap Timbalan Presiden merangkap Perdana Menteri UAE, Pemerintah Dubai, YM Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum di Istana Zabeel, Dubai. https://t.co/1CzpfU2bF5
Translated Text: I was also received before the Deputy President and Prime Minister of the UAE, Ruler of Dubai, YM Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum at Zabeel Palace, Dubai. https://t.co/1CzpfU2bF5

Text: Pertemuan bersama dua pemimpin utama UAE ini saya sifatkan amat berjaya dan cukup berkesan dalam usaha meningkatkan hubungan dua hala antara Malaysia dan UAE ke peringkat lebih tinggi.
Translated Text: I consider this meeting with the two main leaders of the UAE to be very successful and quite effective in the effort to improve bilateral relations between Malaysia and the UAE to a higher level.

Text: Secara amnya perbincangan yang menyentuh kepentingan kedua-dua negara termasuk pelaburan dan perdagangan itu, berjalan lancar sekaligus menterjemahkan  semangat persahabatan yang akrab antara Malaysia dan UAE.
Translated Text: In general, the discussions that touch on the interests of both countries, including investment and trade, went smoothly and translated the spirit of close friendship between Malaysia and the UAE.

Text: Antara kerjasama pelaburan dan perdagangan yang dibincangkan dan dipersetujui ialah peningkatan eksport minyak sawit ke UAE, kerjasama antara PETRONAS dan Abu Dhabi National Oil Company (ADNOC), serta kerjasama dan pelaburan dalam sektor pendidikan negara.
Translated Text: Among the investment and trade cooperation that was discussed and agreed upon was the increase in palm oil exports to the UAE, cooperation between PETRONAS and Abu Dhabi National Oil Company (ADNOC), as well as cooperation and investment in the country's education sector.

Text: Insya-Allah, saya bersama jemaah menteri akan membuat penelitian yang terperinci untuk mengenal pasti bidang dan sektor utama yang berpotensi menarik peniaga dan pelabur asing  bagi meningkatkan ekonomi serta mampu mencipta lebih banyak peluang pekerjaan buat rakyat Malaysia.
Translated Text: God willing, I and the cabinet will conduct a detailed study to identify the main areas and sectors that have the potential to attract foreign traders and investors to improve the economy and create more job opportunities for Malaysians.

Text: Saya berdoa agar semua kerjasama ini dapat kita laksanakan segera dan semoga semuanya berjalan dengan lancar seperti yang telah dirancang.
Translated Text: I pray that we can implement all this cooperation soon and that everything goes smoothly as planned.

Text: @MuhyiddinYassin Tan Sri, saya ada sedikit kegusaran tentang pembukaan sekolah pada 1 Mac ini. Saya berpendapat sekiranya pihak kerajaan dapat menangguh sehingga anak-anak yang bersekolah ini mendapat vaksin. Text: @MuhyiddinYassin Kita ambik iktibar dari PRN di sabah sehingga kes naik begitu mendadak. Nyawa anak-anak ini lebih penting dari pendidikan. Biar lambat belajar tapi sihat dan selamat. Kita sepatutnya fokus pada penambahbaikan PDPR ini.
Translated Text: @MuhyiddinYassin We took a cue from the PRN in Sabah that the cases increased so suddenly. The lives of these children are more important than education. Be slow to learn but be healthy and safe. We should focus on improving this PDPR.

Text: @MuhyiddinYassin Tentang peranti dan internet pada golongan yang kurang berkemampuan di harap kerajaan dapat menyediakan sedikit dana untuk mereka yang memerlukan. Translated Text: @MuhyiddinYassin Regarding devices and internet for the less able, I hope the government can provide some funds for those in need. Focus and empower the modern digitization of children's learning while waiting for a vaccine for them. We do not want cases to increase again

Text: @MuhyiddinYassin Kita memang ada SOP yang ketat tapi mampukah anak2 kita mendisplinkan diri. Sedangkan masa PRN di sabah pun ada SOP tapi kita gagal membendung wabak ini. Translated Text: @MuhyiddinYassin We do have a strict SOP but can our children discipline themselves. While during the PRN in Sabah there was a SOP but we failed to contain this epidemic. Please consider the school opening on March 1. Do not risk the lives of these children. The safest place is at home

Text: Lawatan rasmi atas undangan khas Presiden Indonesia, Joko Widodo (Jokowi) ini amat bermakna dalam mengukuhkan lagi hubungan dua hala Malaysia üá≤üáæ dan Indonesia üáÆüá©. https://t.co/WhtPvElH55
Translated Text: This official visit at the special invitation of the President of Indonesia, Joko Widodo (Jokowi) was very meaningful in strengthening the two-way relations between Malaysia üá≤üáæ and Indonesia üáÆüá©. https://t.co/WhtPvElH55

Text: Pertemuan bersama Bapak Jokowi pada sesi 'veranda talk' merupakan satu lagi pendekatan baharu arena diplomasi antarabangsa dalam situasi pandemik COVID-19. https://t.co/eteBKZUiP1
Translated Text: The meeting with Mr. Jokowi at the 'veranda talk' session is another new approach in the arena of international diplomacy in the situation of the COVID-19 pandemic. https://t.co/eteBKZUiP1

Text: Pada sesi itu, saya membangkit dan mencadangkan langkah ke hadapan dalam beberapa isu seperti pelaburan dan perdagangan, pelaksanaan Laluan Hijau Timbal Balik (RGL), diskriminasi minyak sawit dan kerjasama dalam menangani pandemik COVID-19 serta pergolakan politik semasa Myanmar.
Translated Text: At that session, I raised and proposed steps forward in several issues such as investment and trade, the implementation of the Reciprocal Green Line (RGL), palm oil discrimination and cooperation in dealing with the COVID-19 pandemic as well as the current political unrest in Myanmar.

Text: Bagi pihak Malaysia, saya ingin merakamkan ucapan terima kasih kepada pemerintah Indonesia, khususnya Bapak Presiden Joko Widodo (@jokowi ) atas sambutan amat luar biasa yang diberikan walaupun dalam keadaan pematuhan ketat protokol kesihatan akibat pandemik COVID-19. https://t.co/mYxYcwKCtS
Translated Text: On behalf of Malaysia, I would like to express my gratitude to the Indonesian government, especially Mr. President Joko Widodo (@jokowi) for the extraordinary welcome given despite strict adherence to health protocols due to the COVID-19 pandemic. https://t.co/mYxYcwKCtS

Text: Lawatan ini sangat bermakna apabila dua pemimpin utama negara dapat berbual dan berbincang secara bersemuka selama empat jam dalam satu lawatan rasmi,yang tentunya memberi banyak ruang untuk kami mengorak langkah meningkatkan hubungan sedia ada ke peringkat lebih tinggi.
Translated Text: This visit is very meaningful when the two main leaders of the country can chat and discuss face-to-face for four hours in one official visit, which of course gives us a lot of space to take steps to improve the existing relationship to a higher level.

Text: Berbanding perbincangan secara persidangan video, perbualan kami lebih mesra dan konstruktif, malah beliau meminta saya sentiasa berhubung dengannya bagi membincangkan apa-apa isu berkaitan kepentingan kedua-dua negara. https://t.co/GE9hvsn2A2
Translated Text: Compared to video conference discussions, our conversation was more friendly and constructive, and he even asked me to keep in touch with him to discuss any issues related to the interests of both countries. https://t.co/GE9hvsn2A2

Text: Saya juga berpeluang menunaikan solat Jumaat bersama Bapak Jokowi di Masjid Baiturrahim yang terletak di pekarangan kompleks Istana Merdeka. Khutbah yang dibacakan juga menyentuh mengenai kepentingan vaksinasi menurut perspektif Islam, satu perkara yang turut kami sentuh awalnya
Translated Text: I also had the opportunity to perform Friday prayers with Mr. Jokowi at the Baiturrahim Mosque located in the grounds of the Istana Merdeka complex. The sermon that was read also touched on the importance of vaccination from an Islamic perspective, something we also touched on earlier

Text: Selepas solat, Bapak Jokowi dan saya berjalan kaki dari masjid ke dewan makan untuk memberi lebih ruang kepada kami terus berbincang mengenai hal-hal berkaitan kerjasama antara kedua-dua negara dalam suasana lebih santai. https://t.co/ncjwsUhLzu
Translated Text: After the prayer, Bapak Jokowi and I walked from the mosque to the dining hall to give us more space to continue discussing matters related to cooperation between the two countries in a more relaxed atmosphere. https://t.co/ncjwsUhLzu

Text:
Sewaktu dia berjumpa dengan kami, dia betul2 baru pulang dari hospital, baju hospital juga belum dia tanggal.

Dia beritahu kami dia nak balik ke kampung dan berjumpa dgn keluarganya di sana tapi dia tiada satu sen pun bersama dirinya. Dari situlah dia cerita semuanya kepada kami
Translated Text:
When he met us, he had just returned from the hospital, and he hadn't taken off his hospital clothes.

He told us he wanted to go back to the village and meet his family there but he didn't have a single penny with him. From there he told us everything

Text:
Ah Soon dulu tinggal bersama isterinya dan mengusahakan sebuah kedai makan. tetapi penyakit kanser isterinya makin melarat. Jadi, kedai mrk ditutup dan Ah Soon harus menjaga isterinya sepenuh masa.

Malangnya, penyakit kanser isterinya semakin teruk dan dia meninggal dunia
Translated Text:
Ah Soon used to live with his wife and run a restaurant. but his wife's cancer is getting worse. So, the mrk store is closed and Ah Soon has to take care of his wife full time.

Unfortunately, his wife's cancer worsened and she passed away

Text: Kepergian isterinya telah menjadikan Ah Soon murung. kemurungan dia menjadi teruk sehinggakan dia mengambil keputusan utk ambil nyawanya sendiri dengan memandu kereta secara laju dan akhirnya dia ditimpa kemalangan yang agak teruk. Dia juga koma selepas kemalangan tersebut.
Translated Text: His wife's departure has made Ah Soon depressed. His depression became so bad that he decided to take his own life by driving a car at high speed and finally he got into a serious accident. He was also in a coma after the accident.

Text: Selepas koma jg, penyakit kemurungan semakin teruk. Akibat tekanan hidup yg melampau, dia mengurungkan dirinya di dalam bilik dan mencuba sekali lagi utk mengambil nyawanya, kali ini dengan menelan pil2 yg dibekalkan pihak hospital.
Translated Text: After the coma, depression worsened. As a result of the extreme pressure of life, he locked himself in the room and tried once again to take his life, this time by swallowing the pills provided by the hospital.

Text:
Nasib baik, rakan serumahnya menyedari ketiadaan Ah Soon dan segera mencarinya. Sejurus sahaja melihat Ah Soon yang tidak bermaya di atas lantai biliknya, dia terus bawa Ah Soon ke hospital untuk dapatkan rawatan lanjut.

kalau rakan Ah Soon lambat sedikit sahaja...
Translated Text:
Fortunately, her housemates noticed Ah Soon's absence and immediately looked for her. As soon as he saw Ah Soon who was lifeless on the floor of his room, he immediately took Ah Soon to the hospital for further treatment.

if Ah Soon's friend is just a little late...

Text: Di hospital, dia telah mendapat lanjut. Para doktor menasihati agar dia dijaga oleh keluarganya. Ah Soon akur dan mencari jalan utk pulang. Oleh itu, dia terus ke meminta bantuan dari kami. Dia benar2 mahu pulang ke kampung supaya keluarganya boleh menjaganya.
Translated Text: In the hospital, he has gotten more. The doctors advised that he be looked after by his family. Ah Soon agreed and looked for a way to go home. Therefore, he went straight to asking for help from us. He really wants to go back to the village so that his family can take care of him.

Text: Team kami memahami situasi dia dan membantunya dengan memberikan dia wang belanja dan wang tiket utk pulang ke kampungnya. Sampai sahaja dia di Penang, dia juga telah memberitahu kami.
Translated Text: Our team understood his situation and helped him by giving him shopping money and ticket money to return to his village. As soon as he arrived in Penang, he also told us.

Text:
Saya harap semuanya baik-baik sahaja bagi Ah Soon. Saya faham situasi yang dihadapi olehnya. 

Pandemik ini telah memberikan byk kesan kepada rakyat Malaysia. Di Kepong sahaja sudah banyak kes org mengambil nyawa sendiri.
Translated Text:
I hope all is well for Ah Soon. I understand the situation he is facing.

This pandemic has had a lot of impact on Malaysians. In Kepong alone, there have been many cases of people taking their own lives.

Text: Langkah untuk memansuhkan bunuh diri sebagai jenayah adalah langkah yang wajar sewajar wajarnya. Kita perlu hapuskan stigma berkenaan isu ini. Sudah tiba masanya isu ini dilihat dari segi manusiawi dan bukan dengan diberikan penghukuman.
Translated Text: The move to decriminalize suicide is a perfectly reasonable move. We need to remove the stigma regarding this issue. It is high time that this issue is seen from a humane point of view and not by giving punishment.

Text:
Isu kesihatan mental adalah isu yang sangat perlu diberikan fokus yang lebih oleh kerana ini adalah penyakit yang tidak dapat dilihat dengan mata kasar. Sesiapa sahaja boleh jadi mangsa. 

Saya harap orang di luar sana dapat memahami kepentingan isu ini.
Translated Text:
The issue of mental health is an issue that needs to be given more focus because this is a disease that cannot be seen with the naked eye. Anyone can be a victim.

I hope people out there can understand the importance of this issue.

Text:
Gelembung percutian ini sememangnya inisatif yg bagus, tapi kenapa tidak mahu wajibkan ujian saringan sebelum pergi? 

Walaupun mrk yg akan pergi sudah lengkap dua dos vaksin, mrk masih boleh dijangkiti, lebih2 lagi skrg kita berdepan dgn byk varian baru
Translated Text:
This holiday bubble is indeed a good initiative, but why not make screening tests mandatory before going?

Even if the person who is going to leave has completed two doses of the vaccine, he or she can still be infected, even more so now that we are faced with many new variants

Text:
Apa yg menakutkan adalah sekiranya mrk yg pergi ini bawa virus ke tempat baharu, dan tidak semena-menanya menjadi superspreader tanpa pengetahuan mrk.

Kalau nak masuk tempat kerja baharu pun perlu buat ujian saringan, apatah lagi ke sebuah kawasan baharu utk bercuti.
Translated Text:
What's scary is if the mrk who leaves takes the virus to a new place, and doesn't accidentally become a superspreader without the mrk's knowledge.

If you want to enter a new workplace, you need to take a screening test, let alone go to a new area for vacation.

Text:
Sekurang-kurangnya, mrk yg nak pergi ke pulau tersebut kena buat ujian 48-72 jam sebelum berangkat. Tambahan pula, anak2 bawah umur 18 yg ikut, rata2 mrk belum vaksinasi. 

Kita jg perlu igt, kes positif negara masih ada di dlm jangkauan puluhan ribu, oleh itu -
Translated Text:
At the very least, those who want to go to the island must take a test 48-72 hours before leaving. In addition, the children under the age of 18 who come, on average, have not been vaccinated.

We also need to know, the country's positive cases are still in the range of tens of thousands, therefore -

Text:
-SOP gelembung percutian ini perlu perincikan. 

Secara logiknya jg, lebih selamat agar pelancong tahu status mrk, peniaga2 di pulau juga tidak perlu risau dgn penularan rawak.
Translated Text:
-This holiday bubble soup needs detailing.

Logically, it is safer for tourists to know the status of mrk, traders on the island also do not have to worry about random contagion.

Text:
Saya sambut baik inisiatif ini, tapi "calculated risk" yg diambil perlu diperhalusi lagi. Wajibkan ujian saringan sebelum pergi ke pulau tersebut!

Kita tidak mahu inisiatif ini tersangkut di pertengahan jalan!
Translated Text:
I welcome this initiative, but the "calculated risk" taken needs to be further refined. Obligatory screening test before going to the island!

We don't want this initiative to get stuck in the middle of the road!

Text:

I also gave Mrk a little financial help to buy what he needed.

Text:
Saya rasa wajar utk pentadbiran kementerian wilayah persekutuan, terutamanya DBKL, tubuhkan sebuah "youth council" yg mempunyai kuasa spt jabatan2 dalam DBKL.

Text:
Mula2, team saya igt ini permohonan bantuan biasa, jadi kami pun ambil butiran2 penting. Tapi sedang kami interview, rupanya pakcik tak ada rumah üò∞

Selama ini dia tinggal di kawasan hospital utk memudahkan dia pergi jumpa doktor bagi mendapatkan rawatan dan cuci luka.
Translated Text:
First of all, my team thought this was a normal request for help, so we took the important details. But while we were interviewing, apparently my uncle didn't have a home üò∞

All this time he lived in the hospital area to make it easier for him to go to the doctor to get treatment and clean his wounds.

Text:
Pakcik berasal dari Perak, dan dia turun ke KL utk dapatkan barangan perubatan. Tapi sebab PKP dan sempadan negeri ditutup, dia tak dapat nak balik semula.

Pakcik ni mahir baiki mesin jahit, tapi KL masih dalam PPN fasa 1, dia takda kerja.
Translated Text:
My uncle is from Perak, and he went down to KL to get medical supplies. But because of the MCO and the state border is closed, he can't go back.

This uncle is good at repairing sewing machines, but KL is still in PPN phase 1, he doesn't have a job.

Text:
Selama ini juga, dia bergantung makanan dari dapur-dapur jalanan sekitar. Dan kalau dia nak mandi, dia akan pergi ke tandas awam. 

Pihak kami offer dia utk dia tinggal di sebuah pusat jagaan org tua di Kepong, sekurang-kurangnya, dia ada tempat tinggal. 

Akan tetapi -
Translated Text:
All this time, he depended on food from nearby street kitchens. And if he wants to take a shower, he will go to the public toilet.

We offer him to live in a care center for the elderly in Kepong, at least, he has a place to live.

But -

Text: dia tidak mahu. Bilangnya, sebagai seorang yg kerap ke hospital, dia tidak mahu membawak virus pulang ke tempat itu. Dia juga tak mahu menyusahkan org lain. Selagi dia mampu utk uruskan dirinya, dia akan cuba sehabis baik.
Translated Text: he doesn't want to. He said, as someone who often goes to the hospital, he does not want to bring the virus back to that place. He also does not want to trouble other people. As long as he is able to take care of himself, he will try his best.

Text:
kami menghormati keputusannya. Kami pun belikan dia dua buah tiub. Satu tiub boleh tahan dalam sebulan.  Kami juga berikan dia sedikit duit belanja.

Harapan dia hanya utk pindah semula ke kampungnya dan jalani kerja seperti biasa setelah fasa PPN berubah.
Translated Text:
we respect his decision. We also bought him two tubes. One tube can last a month. We also gave him some shopping money.

His only hope is to move back to his village and work as usual after the VAT phase changes.

Text: Bagi pihak saya, kami sentiasa sedia menghulurkan bantuan. Kami beritahu dia kalau ada apa2, dia boleh cari kami üôÇ
Translated Text: For my part, we are always ready to lend a helping hand. We told him if there is anything, he can find us üôÇ

Text: Saya percaya kerajaan mampu utk subsidikan test kit ini. kalau kerajaan boleh beli vaksin untuk semua orang di Malaysia, sudah tentu test kit kendiri ini juga boleh diberikan.
Translated Text: I believe the government is able to subsidize this test kit. if the government can buy vaccines for everyone in Malaysia, of course this self-test kit can also be given.

Text:
tambahan pula, sektor ekonomi kita pula sudah slow2 buka, sudah tentunya ada keperluan utk org ramai selalu buat ujian saringan kendiri.

Rakyat kita juga masih lagi ada yang tidak divaksinasikan dan kes harian juga masih tinggi.
Translated Text:
In addition, our economic sector has been slow to open, of course there is a need for people to always do self-screening tests.

Our people are also still unvaccinated and daily cases are still high.

Text: Di UK, mereka sedang cuba untuk budayakan ujian kendiri ini setiap dua minggu bagi sesiapa yang mahu melakukannya. Saya rasa ini langkah yg bagus yg kerajaan kita patut ikut.
Translated Text: In the UK, they are trying to culture this self-test every two weeks for anyone who wants to do it. I think this is a good step that our government should follow.

Text: Lagipun, hal ini akan membantu pihak KKM di dalam metode "identify & isolate" mereka. Mereka yg dah buat test boleh cepat2 kuarantin kendiri.
Translated Text: After all, this will help the Ministry of Health in their "identify & isolate" method. Those who have taken the test can self-quarantine quickly.

Text:
Kita perlu usahakan segala macam cara dan usaha untuk memutuskan rantaian COVID-19 di Malaysia. 

Semakin hari, semakin risau saya dengan varian-varian baru yg wujud. 

The war against COVID-19 is also a war against time.
Translated Text:
We need to do all kinds of ways and efforts to break the chain of COVID-19 in Malaysia.

Day by day, I am more and more worried about the new variants that exist.

The war against COVID-19 is also a war against time.

Text:
Antara sebab2 popular ada org tolak vaksin:

1. Tak mahu masukkan bendasing ke dalam badan mrk
2. Tidak percaya dengan keberkesanan vaksin
3. Vaksin adalah perubatan bermotif jahat (freemason, illuminati dll)

dan ini adalah isu yang sedang berlaku di seantero dunia

2/9
Translated Text:
Among the popular reasons there are people who reject vaccines:

1. I don't want to put foreign bodies in my body
2. Do not believe in the effectiveness of vaccines
3. Vaccines are medicine with evil motives (freemasons, illuminati etc.)

and this is an issue that is happening all over the world

2/9

Text:
Walaupun kita ada langkah2 utk tangani isu ini, (denda utk mereka yg sebar berita palsu berkaitan vaksin), tapi usaha ini terlihat spt tidak rancak.

Kalau di FB, kita sudah lihat trend di mana org ramai menukar perkataan vaksin kepada perkataan spt meksin, beksin, dll

3/9
Translated Text:
Although we have measures to deal with this issue, (fines for those who spread false news related to vaccines), but this effort seems to be slow.

If on FB, we have seen a trend where many people change the word vaccine to words like meksin, beksin, etc

3/9

Text:
Apa yg merisaukan adalah yg menidakkan vaksin ini bukan calang2 org. Mrk ini ada pengaruh tersendiri dalam komuniti. selebriti dan agamawan misalnya. 

Jika dibiarkan, isu ini pasti melarat, lebih2 lagi peratusan vaksinasi M'sia sudah menghampiri sasaran imuniti kelompok. 

4/9
Translated Text:
What's troubling is that it's not the people who cancel this vaccine. This Mrk has its own influence in the community. celebrities and religious people for example.

If left unchecked, this issue will surely worsen, more than 2 percent of M'sia vaccinations are approaching the group immunity target.

4/9

Text:
Walaupun "surge vaccination" telah membantu mencapai peratusan vaksin yg kita lihat hari ini, usaha giat utk mmenyampaikan info berkaitan vaksin itu perlu

Kita harus faham isu yg kita sedang berdepan sekarang ini adalah isu yg sekian lamanya dihadapi oleh komuniti perubatan

5/9
Translated Text:
Although the "vaccination surge" has helped achieve the percentage of vaccines we see today, efforts to convey information related to the vaccine are necessary

We must understand that the issue we are facing now is an issue that has been faced by the medical community for a long time

5/9

Text:
"Vaccine hesitancy" adalah masalah yg perlu ditangani secara efektif. 

Usaha memberikan informasi berkenaan vaksin kini tidak boleh dilakukan secara dasar. Pendekatan khusus perlu diambil bagi memastikan orang awam yakin dengan vaksin.

6/9
Translated Text:
"Vaccine hesitancy" is a problem that needs to be dealt with effectively.

Efforts to provide information about vaccines are now basically impossible. A specific approach needs to be taken to ensure public confidence in the vaccine.

6/9

Text:
Misalnya:

-Kerjasama dgan badan2/individu tertentu yang mempunyai pengaruh perlu dijalankan secara berkala bagi memastikan mrk boleh menarik minat org ramai utk mengambil vaksin.

-Insentif dari pihak kerajaan bagi mrk yg mengambil suntikan vaksin

7/9
Translated Text:
For example:

-Collaboration with certain bodies/individuals who have influence should be carried out periodically to ensure that the brand can attract the interest of many people to take the vaccine.

-Incentives from the government for those who take vaccinations

7/9

Text:
-Perancangan penerangan yang holistik yang mengasimilasikan lokaliti, budaya, bangsa &  latar belakang masyarakat.

-mewajibkan pengambilan vaksin bagi sektor2 yg melibatkan pergaulan dengan org awam 

-denda lebih tinggi utk mrk yg sebar berita palsu mengenai vaksin

8/9
Translated Text:
-Holistic information planning that assimilates locality, culture, race & community background.

-mandatory vaccination for sectors that involve socializing with the public

-higher fines for brands that spread fake news about vaccines

8/9

Text:
Perjalanan kita dalam menangani krisis pandemik covid-19 sebenarnya masih jauh. Oleh yg demikian, kita perlu usaha2 yg jelas dan berterusan bagi menangani isu 'vaccine hesitancy' ini.

jangan sampai sudah ada komuniti sembah cengkih baru kita mahu bertindak.

9/9
Translated Text:
Our journey in dealing with the covid-19 pandemic crisis is actually still far. Therefore, we need clear and continuous efforts to deal with this 'vaccine hesitancy' issue.

don't wait until there is a new clove worshiping community we want to act.

9/9

Text:
Nak senangkan cerita sy namakan dia Shin (bukan nama sebenar)

Shin was diagnosed with a spine tumor early this year. Bcs of it, some part of his muscles are shrinking & sekarang dia terpaksa bertongkat.

Dlm masa yg sama, he is relying heavily on his mother, who is also an oku.
Translated Text:
Want to make the story easier, I named him Shin (not his real name)

Shin was diagnosed with a spine tumor early this year. Bcs of it, some part of his muscles are shrinking & now he was forced to stick.

In the same time, he is relying heavily on his mother, who is also an oku.

Text:
Sebelum pkp, shin & abgnya boleh bekerja utk menyara keluarga kecil mrk.

Tapi semenjak sakit dan pkp, dia tiada pendapatan dan abgnya juga mempunyai masalah kewangan.

He wants to do something for the mum, but cant really do much due to his situation, hence the request.
Translated Text:
Before pkp, shin & His brother can work to support his small family.

But since the illness and pkp, he has no income and his brother also has financial problems.

He wants to do something for the mum, but can't really do much due to his situation, hence the request.

Text:
Sy beli cake supaya shin boleh menyambut jadi ibunya. 

Saya faham pkp ini sgt mencabar. Kita sudah hampir sebulan hidup dlm keadaan yg terkurung. Its sad that not everyone can find pockets of happiness during this trying time.

I hope my small gift helps. https://t.co/GunzP7eYhX
Translated Text:
I bought a cake so that Shin could celebrate becoming his mother.

I understand this pkp is very challenging. We have been living in confinement for almost a month. Its sad that not everyone can find pockets of happiness during this trying time.

I hope my little gift helps. https://t.co/GunzP7eYhX

Text:
Dulu en. Syakier bawa teksi. Tapi semenjak kemalangan beberapa tahun lepas yg menyebabkan tulang belakangnya terkesan dgn teruk, dia mempunyai masalah pergerakan. 

Ada harinya dia boleh berjalan, ada hari dia terlantar. Waktu sy lawat dia sebentar tadi, dia sedang berehat.
Translated Text:
It used to be Mr. Syakier takes a taxi. But since an accident a few years ago that severely damaged his spine, he has mobility problems.

Some days he can walk, some days he is bedridden. When I visited him a while ago, he was resting.

Text:
En. Syakier ni rajin orangnya. Dalam keadaan begini pun dia masih menjalankan perniagaan kerepeknya.

Dia bagitahu kdg2 dia malu mahu minta bantuan. Tapi baru2 ini, dia terpaksa kibarkan bendera putih kerana keadaannya yg sudah terdesak https://t.co/hs2w4J1ruK
Translated Text:
Mr. Syakier is a hardworking person. Even in this situation, he still runs his chip business.

He told kdg2 he was embarrassed to ask for help. But recently, he had to wave the white flag because of his desperate situation https://t.co/hs2w4J1ruK

Text:
Sy bagitahu en. Syakier tak perlu malu. Kalau perlukan bantuan, hubungi saja pihak sy. Sy cuba bantu semampu boleh.

En. Syakier skrg ini sdg menyara 2 org anaknya.
Translated Text:
I told Mr. Syakier does not need to be ashamed. If you need help, just contact me. I try to help as much as I can.

Mr. Syakier is now supporting his 2 children.

Text:
Sebelum ini, sy telah berjanji utk membantu en syakier dgn bantuan kewangan selama 3 bulan, hari ini saya serahkan bantuan utk bulan yg seterusnya.

Kalau kalian nak membantu, belilah kerepek dari en. Syakier. Fav sy adalah rempeyek dia. Crunchy giler! https://t.co/lC3CJDGbLp
Translated Text:
Before this, I promised to help Mr. Syakier with financial assistance for 3 months, today I am handing over the assistance for the next month.

If you want to help, buy chips from Mr. Shakier. My fav is his rempeyek. Crazy crunchy! https://t.co/lC3CJDGbLp

Text:

Text:
kalau kita ikut spesifikasi tersebut, kita hanya mampu bantu keluarga yg hanya 5-6 ahli. Keluarga yg dalam lingkungan belasan org macam mana pula? 

Dekat Kepong pun ada keluarga yang sampai 15 org duduk satu rumah. Bekalan macam ni takkan cukup
Translated Text:
if we follow the specification, we can only help families with only 5-6 members. What about a family of around a dozen people?

Near Kepong there are families with up to 15 people living in one house. This kind of supply will not be enough

Text:
Dengan bakul one-off ini, berapa lama agaknya bekalan ini akan akan tahan? Saya rasa paling2 pun seminggu sahaja.

Bagaimana dgn keluarga yg ada bayi kecil yg perlukan lampin dan susu bayi? Dalam list yg berikan brg2 bayi tak ada
Translated Text:
With this one-off basket, how long do you think this supply will last? I think at least a week.

What about families with small babies who need diapers and baby milk? In the list given, there are no baby numbers

Text:
Semenjak PKP tempoh hari, berpuluh2 keluarga minta kpd saya bantuan susu bayi dan lampin. Bukan kita tak pernah dgr kisah ibu2 terpaksa beri anak2 susu pekat!

Belum lagi campur mrk yg mahu beli ubat dan barang2 keperluan lain yg spesifik.
Translated Text:
Since the MCO period, dozens of families have asked me for help with baby milk and diapers. It's not that we have never heard stories of mothers having to give their children condensed milk!

Not to mention the mix of brands that want to buy medicine and other specific necessities.

Text: Cadangan saya mudah, berikan duit tersebut kpd pusat khidmat parlimen, dan biar parlimen tersebut yg tentukan bagaimana cara duit tersebut akan dibelanjakan.
Translated Text: My suggestion is simple, give the money to the parliamentary service center, and let the parliament decide how the money will be spent.

Text: Setiap parlimen pasti ada perkara utama yg perlu diutamakan. Oleh itu, wajar utk ahli parlimen tentukan bagaimana wang tersebut akan dibelanjakan.
Translated Text: Every parliament must have the main things that need to be prioritized. Therefore, it is appropriate for members of parliament to determine how the money will be spent.

Text:
Untuk parlimen Kepong, rancangan saya adalah utk duit tersebut diuruskan dalam bentuk baucar beli belah, dijalankan dengan kerjasama kedai-kedai terpilih di dalam kawasan parlimen.

Peniaga2 kecil pun perlukan bantuan buat ketika ini.
Translated Text:
For the Kepong parliament, my plan is for the money to be managed in the form of shopping vouchers, carried out in collaboration with selected shops within the parliamentary area.

Small traders also need help at this time.

Text:
Dengan baucar tersebut, penerima boleh beli apa sahaja mereka mahu mengikut keperluan masing2. 

Mana2 keluarga yg memerlukan bantuan lebih, kita juga boleh berikan.

Kita beri peluang utk mrk pilih apa yg mereka mahu beli.
Translated Text:
With the voucher, the recipient can buy whatever they want according to their needs.

Any family that needs more help, we can also give it.

We give the opportunity for the brand to choose what they want to buy.

Text:
Dalam situasi ini, kita bukan sahaja membantu rakyat, tetapi kita juga membantu peniaga2 kecil kita untuk ‚Äòstay afloat‚Äô. 

If we can come up with a ‚Äòwin-win‚Äô situation, we should strive for that.
Translated Text:
In this situation, we not only help the people, but we also help our small traders to 'stay afloat'.

If we can come up with a 'win-win' situation, we should strive for that.

Text:
When i asked some of them, ada yg mahu ditolong dan ada yg tak, walaupun sudah dipujuk.

In such situation, i cannot force them. I can only help those who wants to be helped.

That was also the night i met Ah Man (bukan nama betul)
Translated Text:
When i asked some of them, ada yg mahu ditolong dan ada yg tak, walaupun sudah dipujuk.

In such situation, i cannot force them. I can only help those who wants to be helped.

That was also the night i met Ah Man (bukan nama betul)

Text:
Ah Man beritahu sy, he has been sleeping on the streets ever since the first PKP. He has no money to pay for his room's rent.

Dulu bekerja sebagai tukang baiki aircond, tapi kini tidak bekerja kerana tempat kerja lamanya tidak mampu membayar gajinya.
Translated Text:
Ah Man told me, he has been sleeping on the streets ever since the first PKP. He has no money to pay for his room's rent.

He used to work as an aircond repairman, but now he doesn't work because his old workplace can't afford to pay his salary.

Text:
Dalam tempoh 5 bulan ini jg, he has been scavenging for food in the garbage as well as catching fish in the river. üò∞

Untuk dapat wang tambahan, dia akan cari sampah yang boleh dikitar semula. Kadang2 dengan duit tersebut dia akan beli makanan.
Translated Text:
During these 5 months as well, he has been scavenging for food in the garbage as well as catching fish in the river. üò∞

To get extra money, he will look for trash that can be recycled. Sometimes with that money he will buy food.

Text:
As a young man, I believe that he has a bright future ahead of him. 

It is devastating for me to see him spending his early adulthood on the streets.

Sy tanya dia sekiranya dia mahu dibantu, dan pada awalnya dia malu. Bilangnya tak mahu susahkan siapa2.
Translated Text:
As a young man, I believe that he has a bright future ahead of him.

It is devastating for me to see him spending his early adulthood on the streets.

Sy asked him if he wanted help, and at first he was shy. He said he didn't want to trouble anyone.

Text: selepas beberapa ketika memujuk, akhirnya dia akur. Saya bawa dia ke pusat khidmat saya untuk mengambil butiran tentang dirinya. https://t.co/T1LXgfTy3H
Translated Text: after some persuasion, he finally agreed. I took him to my service center to take details about him. https://t.co/T1LXgfTy3H

Text:
Waktu itu sudah agak lewat, jadi sy tempatkan dia di sebuah hotel utk dia berehat. 

Cadangan seterusnya adalah utk mengaturkan temuduga kerja utknya.

Sebagai seorang yg mahir dalam bidang baiki alat, byk peluang pekerjaan utknya. https://t.co/Pszu46X7VG
Translated Text:
It was quite late, so I put him in a hotel for him to rest.

The next suggestion is to arrange a job interview for him.

As someone who is skilled in the field of repairing tools, there are many job opportunities for him. https://t.co/Pszu46X7VG

Text:
Syukur juga, sy ada kenalan yg sedang mencari org utk bekerja dengan dia dalam bidang yg dia pernah ceburi dulu!

The next morning, selepas check-out, Ah Man telah menghadiri sesi temuduga kerja yg dilakukan di pusat khidmat sy.

Sekarang ini, pihak sy hanya menunggu jawapan :) https://t.co/nCxR2XiMOS
Translated Text:
Thank goodness, I have a friend who is looking for someone to work with him in the field he used to dabble in!

The next morning, after check-out, Ah Man attended a job interview session conducted at my service center.

Right now, my side is just waiting for an answer :) https://t.co/nCxR2XiMOS

Text:
bantuan yg sy tawarkan kpd Ah Man ini adalah sebahagian drpd operasi sy membantu golongan gelandangan di Kepong.

Setiap insan wajar diberikan peluang kedua, dan sekiranya mereka mahu dibantu, bantuan wajar diberikan

Every person should be given a second chance, and if they want help, help should be given

Text:
Puan Sun hidup dengan mengharapkan duit daripada @JKMHQ. 

Tetapi baru2 ini, disebabkan oleh cap jarinya tidak boleh diimbas sistem, dia tidak dpt mengemas kini datanya.

Pihak jkm menyuruh dia utk pergi ke JPN utk selesaikan isu tersebut.
Translated Text:
Puan Sun lives by expecting money from @JKMHQ.

But recently, due to his fingerprint not being scanned by the system, he was unable to update his data.

The jkm told him to go to JPN to resolve the issue.

Text: Masalahnya, JPN tidak beroperasi di waktu PKP ini. Jadinya, dia tidak lagi menerima bantuan kewangan dari pihak @JKMHQ atas masalah ini.
Translated Text: The problem is, JPN does not operate during this MCO. So, he no longer receives financial assistance from @JKMHQ due to this problem.

Text: Buat masa ini, sy beritahu Puan Sun yang sy akan membantunya. Saya beri dia angpow supaya dia dapat beli apa-apa keperluan untuk dirinya.
Translated Text: For now, I told Mrs. Sun that I would help her. I gave him angpow so he could buy anything he needed.

Text:
Apa yg sy ingin highlight di sini adalah apakah masalah spt ini tidak dapat dijangkakan oleh pihak @JKMHQ?

Bila org yg memerlukan mcm Pn Sun menghadapi masalah seperti ini, bagaimana dia mahu teruskan kehidupan?

Pkp pun kita tak tahu habis bila, jadi bila dia boleh dpt bantuan?
Translated Text:
What I want to highlight here is whether a problem like this could not be foreseen by @JKMHQ?

When a needy person like Ms. Sun faces problems like this, how does she want to continue living?

We don't even know when it will end, so when can he get help?

Text:
Banyak juga badan2 ngo yg tidak dapat kelulusan daripada @JKMHQ utk lakukan kerja2 kebajikan atas alasan PKP ini. 

Sepatutnya mereka patut dibenarkan utk beroperasi!

Kalau bukan mrk, siapa yg akan membantu golongan rentan ini?
Translated Text:
There are also many NGOs who cannot get approval from @JKMHQ to do charity work because of this MCO.

They should be allowed to operate!

If not mrk, who will help this vulnerable group?

Text:
Mohon ada jawapan dari pihak berwajib! Rancakkan kerja-kerja kebajikan utk rakyat di waktu PKP ini! 

Jangan hanya mahu tunggu dan datang ke pejabay yang entah bila bukak untuk mohon bantuan!
Translated Text:
Please have an answer from the authorities! Stimulate welfare work for the people during this MCO period!

Don't just want to wait and come to a pejabay that doesn't know when it opens to ask for help!

Text:
Sepatutnya, dalam tempoh yg meruncing spt skrg, @JKMHQ patut ubah cara membantu mrk yg memerlukan!

Tak boleh lagi tunggu org datang dan minta bantuan! 

Langkah proaktif perlu diambil bagi mengenal pasti org2 yg perlukan bantuan segera, lagi2 dalam tempoh PKP ini!
Translated Text:
It should be, in a period like the current one, @JKMHQ should change the way to help those in need!

Can't wait for people to come and ask for help!

Proactive steps need to be taken to identify people who need immediate help, again during this MCO period!

Text:
As an mp, there is so much i can do for the people in my constituent, let alone from others,

Individuals from different constituencies requesting help from a elected rep in a faraway constituent is an alarming sign that the gov is not doing enough for the people in need!

Text:
Kebarangkalian pkp ini utk terus disambung tinggi,

Dan dari situ juga kita boleh anggar yg ramai lagi akan hilang tempat utk bergantung.

Sampai bila nak terus biarkan macam ni? Nyawa rakyat boleh digadaikan macamtu saja?
Translated Text:
The probability that this pkp will continue to be extended is high,

And from there we can estimate that many more will lose a place to depend on.

How long do you want to keep it like this? People's lives can be pawned just like that?

Text:
penurunan kes dari 5k ke 4k lebih dilihat sebagai sebuah kejayaan.

Ini adalah kenyataan yg tak langsung memahami keadaan semasa yg semakin kritikal dan walaupun adanya penurunan, nyawa orang ramai telah menjadi korban dan masih ada yg akan menjadi korban!
Translated Text:
the decrease in cases from 5k to 4k is more seen as a success.

This is a statement that does not directly understand the current situation which is becoming more critical and despite the decline, people's lives have been sacrificed and there are still some who will be sacrificed!

Text:
Mrk sudah tidak byr sewa 2 bulan. Makan pun kdg kala perlu mrk catu. 

Disebabkan penyakit2 Pn Ching Hua juga, mrk terpaksa ulang alik ke hospital utk mendapatkan rawatan, lebih2 lagi utk rawatan susulan kanser rahim yg dialami oleh Pn Ching Hua.
Translated Text:
Mrk has not paid rent for 2 months. Eat when you need to get rations.

Due to Ms. Ching Hua's illnesses, she had to go back and forth to the hospital to get treatment, especially for the follow-up treatment of uterine cancer that Ms. Ching Hua suffered.

Text:
Sy tahu perihal keadaan kondisi mrk selepas Pn Ching Hua menghantar mesej di FB pada suatu malam. 

Sejurus dapat mesej tersebut, pihak saya telah menguruskan apa yang patut bagi membantu keluarga dia.
Translated Text:
Sy found out about Mrk's condition after Ms. Ching Hua sent a message on FB one night.

As soon as I got the message, I took care of everything to help his family.

Text:
Selain bantuan makanan, sy juga telah membantu menyelesaikan sewa rumah mrk yg tertunggak.

Dalam kes Hisham, sy sdg cuba utk mencari kerja kosong, supaya dia dpt mencari pendapatan utk keluarganya.

Sy jg akan membantu mrk utk mohon bantuan JKM dan Baitulmal
Translated Text:
In addition to food assistance, I have also helped settle the outstanding house rent.

In Hisham's case, I am trying to find a vacant job, so that he can earn an income for his family.

I will also help Mrk to apply for help from JKM and Baitulmal

Text:
Hanya mahu cerita, Pn Ching Hua menjadikan Hisham anak angkat ketika umur hisham 18 tahun.

ketika itu, dia hidup merempat. Hidupnya jadi begitu selepas ibu bapanya meninggal ketika umurnya 15 tahun.
Translated Text:
Just want to tell a story, Ms. Ching Hua adopted Hisham when Hisham was 18 years old.

at that time, he lived on four. His life became like that after his parents died when he was 15 years old.

Text:
Sewaktu dia menjadi gelandangan, dia akan pergi ke sana sini utk mencari kerja. Tapi ketika itu susah utk dia dapat kerja kerana dia masih kecil.

Kesian juga apabila dengar, umur sebegitu dah hadapi cabaran hidup yg begitu brutal
Translated Text:
When he was homeless, he would go here and there to find work. But at that time it was difficult for him to get a job because he was still young.

It's also a shame to hear that such a young age has faced such a brutal life challenge

Text:
Dia jg beritahu saya pernah ada ketika, dia membeli sebungkus gula, dan hanya makan satu sudu gula utk setiap hari, semata-mata utk isi perut.

Sampai begitu sekali.....
Translated Text:
He also told me that there was a time when he bought a packet of sugar, and only ate one spoonful of sugar every day, just to fill his stomach.

Until then.....

Text:
Waktu dia dipertemukan dgn Pn Ching Hua, ketika itu dia meminta bantuan makanan.

Kerana kasihankan keadaannya, Pn Ching Hua membantunya. Dan apabila dia dapat tahu Hisham seorang anak yatim, dia menganggap Hisham anak angkatnya dan menjaganya.
Translated Text:
When he met Pn Ching Hua, that's when he asked for help with food.

Taking pity on his situation, Ms. Ching Hua helped him. And when he found out Hisham was an orphan, he considered Hisham his adopted son and took care of him.

Text:
Sewaktu saya jumpa mereka, hubungan mrk saling tak tumpah, macam seorang ibu kandung dengan anaknya. Hisham juga memanggil Pn Ching Hua 'mak'

Biar berlainan cara pertuturan, warna kulit dan agama, kalau dah sayang tu, sayang saja. https://t.co/3y6nsFib65

Text:
Cabaran adik Safiya besar, tahun ni dia akan duduki SPM, jadi byk persediaan yang perlu dilakukan.

Dan stres belajar online ni bukan biasa2. Nampak senang tetapi usaha mrk letak bukan biasa2.

Saya duduk depan laptop sahaja sudah penat.
Translated Text:
Safiya's sister's challenge is big, this year she will sit for SPM, so a lot of preparation needs to be done.

And the stress of studying online is not normal. It seems easy, but Mrk's efforts are unusual.

I'm just sitting in front of the laptop and I'm tired.

Text:
kita belum lagi sentuh isu internet. Adik Safiya dan adik2nya melanggan internet sebyk rm5 seminggu. Itu pun mrk pakai untuk kegunaan check kerja sahaja.

Bagaimana pula dengan zoom/gmeet class? platform seperti itu for sure makan byk data
Translated Text:
we have not yet touched the internet issue. Safiya's sister and her sisters subscribe to the internet for rm5 a week. Even that is only used for checking work.

How about a zoom/gmeet class? Such a platform for sure eats a lot of data

Text:
kalau tak silap sy, kelas 1 jam zoom/gmeet adalah lebih kurang dalam 1GB. Dan 1GB adalah lebih kurang belasan ringgit.

Paling2 perlu bayar lebih kurang internet yg berharga rm80 utk sebulan.

itu utk seorang, bagaimana pula dengan mrk yg mempunyai anak yg ramai?
Translated Text:
If I'm not mistaken, a 1-hour zoom/gmeet class is approximately 1GB. And 1GB is about a dozen ringgit.

Most need to pay for internet which costs rm80 for a month.

that's for one person, what about mrk who has many children?

Text:
Walaupun di luar sana ada pelan internet murah, tetapi bagi kebanyakan keluarga B40, RM50 sebulan juga dikira mahal.

Ada ibu bapa bergolok-gadai semua yg mrk ada, sampaikan berhutang dengan ahlong, semata-mata utk membeli smartphone/tablet utk anak2.
Translated Text:
Although there are cheap internet plans out there, but for most B40 families, RM50 per month is also considered expensive.

There are parents who pawn everything they have, saying they are in debt, just to buy smartphones/tablets for their children.

Text:
Sy masih hairan, mana pergi laptop yg dijanjikan kerajaan? 

Sampai bila nak biarkan anak2 kita terkapai-kapai dalam pelajaran.

Sikap acuh tak acuh pihak kerajaan ini sudah melampau! Sudahlah begitu, tiada pelan kukuh utk pendidikan anak2 di Malaysia!
Translated Text:
I'm still wondering, where did the laptop promised by the government go?

Until when do we want to let our children go wild in their studies.

The government's indifference is extreme! That's it, there is no solid plan for children's education in Malaysia!

Text:
anak2 di Kepong yg melalui masalah yg sama, beritahu sy. Sy akan cuba termampu saya utk provide apa yg boleh.

Sy faham PKP bukan waktu mudah utk semua. Sy minta utk tidak malu minta bantuan dari pihak berwajib. Hubungi saya di FB. 

Akan sy cuba bantu mrk yg perlu!
Translated Text:
Children in Kepong who are going through the same problem, tell me. I will try my best to provide what I can.

I understand that MCO is not an easy time for everyone. I ask you not to be ashamed to ask for help from the authorities. Contact me on FB.

Text:
sebelum ini, dia akan pergi ke kawasan2 sekitar Kepong utk jual kerepek. Tapi bulan puasa lepas, dia bekerja terlalu keras sampai sakit tulang belakang dia melarat.

Semenjak dari itu, dia byk habiskan masa di atas katil utk rehat. disebakan itu juga, jualannya terjejas teruk
Translated Text:
before, he would go to areas around Kepong to sell chips. But last fasting month, he worked too hard until his spine hurt.

Since then, he spends a lot of time on the bed to rest. because of that, sales were severely affected

Text:
sewaktu sy lawat dia, dia malu. Dia kata dia taknak susahkan siapa2. Dia cuba cari cara untuk jual kerepek2 dia. Perihal keadaan dia pun, kawan dia yg beritahu sy.

Sebelum ni, pihak sy ada bantu dia utk beli barang2 utk dia mula niaga. Dan selalu juga staf saya beli dari dia.
Translated Text:
when I visit him, he is shy. He said he doesn't want to trouble anyone. He is trying to find a way to sell his chips. About his situation, his friend told him.

Before this, my side helped him to buy things for him to start a business. And my staff always buy from him.

Text:
Terkesan juga bila dia cakap, ada hari dia tak makan sebab tak boleh jual apa-apa. 

Kalau boleh dia taknak bergantung dengan bantuan sepanjang masa, sebab dia masih bertanggungjawab utk membesarkan anak2 dia.

Syukur juga sy dipertemukan semula dengan en. Syakier. Kalau tak -
Translated Text:
It was also impressive when he said that there were days when he didn't eat because he couldn't sell anything.

If possible, he doesn't want to depend on help all the time, because he is still responsible for raising his children.

I'm also grateful to be reunited with Mr. Shakier. If not -

Text:
- sy mungkin tak tahu keadaan dia skrg macam mana

Dia ada dapat bantuan dari @JKMHQ, sekarang dia tgh tunggu jwpn perihal rumah sewa ppr @DBKL2u.

Apply PPR dari bulan dec 2020 tapi masih belum ada jawapan lagi.

dia juga masih dalam proses memohon SSM
Translated Text:
- I may not know how he is now

He got help from @JKMHQ, now he's waiting for a reply about the rental house ppr @DBKL2u.

Apply PPR from December 2020 but still no answer yet.

he is also still in the process of applying for SSM

Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u Buat masa ini, sy beritahu en. Syakier saya akan bantu dgn beri bantuan kewangan utk 3 bulan ini.

Elaun mp sy digunakan utk bantu dia harungi waktu2 mencabar ini. Pkp tak boleh gerak ke sana sini, sudah pasti nya jualannya terjejas teruk.
Translated Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u For now, I told Mr. Syakier I will help by giving financial assistance for these 3 months.

My mp allowance is used to help him get through these challenging times. Pkp can't move here and there, it's certain that sales will be badly affected.

Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u Sy juga berikan sedikit bantuan makanan. Harapnya membantu lah sedikit.

Pihak sy juga mengambil maklum permohonan2 bantuan yg dia sudah mohon dan akan cuba bantu yg mana boleh dibantu.
Translated Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u Sy also give me some help with food. Hope it helps a little.

My side also takes note of the requests for help that he has already applied for and will try to help those who can be helped.

Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u Pkp ni nak buat gathering bagi  bantuan susah sikit. Jadi saya pergi lawat rumah2 org yg memerlukan.

Bila pergi tempat2 mcm ni baru kita tahu keadaan sebenar, dan tahu apa yg perlu dilakukan.
Translated Text:
@JKMHQ @DBKL2u The Pkp wants to hold a gathering for a little help. So I went to visit the homes of people in need.

When we go to places like this, we only know the real situation, and know what needs to be done.

Text:
semalam, saya ada tonton video pasal sekumpulan pekerja pembersihan yg minta naik gaji

sedih tgk situasi mrk. Kerja sudahlah tak berhenti, bayaran pula sikit.

Kejilah org yang memperhambakan mereka ini!
Translated Text:
Yesterday, I watched a video about a group of cleaning workers asking for a raise

sad about the situation Mr. The work is non-stop, the pay is low.

Disgrace the people who enslave them!

Text:
kalau waktu pandemik ni, kerja mereka around the clock. Kerja pun boleh tahan bahaya. 

Acik2 cleaner hospital tu, sentiasa terdedah pada covid19. Tapi tak dapat vaksin.

Tak payahkan vaksin, Rm600 elaun frontliners pun mrk tak dapat!

Apesal ek kerajaan?
Translated Text:
during this pandemic, they work around the clock. Even work can withstand danger.

Those hospital cleaners are always exposed to covid19. But can't get the vaccine.

Don't worry about the vaccine, the Rm600 frontliners allowance doesn't even get it!

What about the government?

Text:
abg2 dan acik2 guard pun sama. Hari-hari jumpa org, tapi takda consideration langsung untuk beri mereka vaksin.

Ahli parlimen yg tak bersidang kau vaksinkan pulak. Apa logik?
Translated Text:
Brother and sister, the guards are the same. I see people every day, but there is no direct consideration to give them the vaccine.

You vaccinate parliamentarians who are not in session. What is the logic?

Text:
Dah tiba masa untuk mrk ni dikira sebagai frontliners, kerja-kerja mrk bahaya!

vaksinkan mereka, tak kira warganegara! Mereka wajar dapat perlindungan!
Translated Text:
It's time for these brands to be considered as frontliners, their work is dangerous!

vaccinate them, regardless of nationality! They deserve protection!

Text:
Amalan rasuah dlm kalangan segelintir anggota polis bukanlah perkara yang baharu.

kes-kes macam ni byk dah kita dengar dari orang di sekeliling kita.

Nak cerita berapa lama, 40 tahun lamanya perkara seperti ini sudah jadi.
Translated Text:
Corruption among a few police officers is not a new thing.

We have heard many cases like this from people around us.

I want to tell you how long, for 40 years things like this have been happening.

Text:
Siapa yang selalu jadi mangsa anggota yang tak berintegriti ini?

banyak kes yg melibatkan pekerja2 asing.

Duit yang polis korup ni ugut dari pekerja asing ni pula kadang kala jumlahnya banyak.

Sampai ribu-ribu pun ada.
Translated Text:
Who is always the victim of this dishonest member?

many cases involving foreign workers.

The money that the corrupt police extort from these foreign workers is sometimes a lot.

There are even thousands.

Text:
minggu lepas, rakan saya telah berdepan dengan insiden malang yang melibatkan polis korup.

teman wanitanya (warga indonesia) telah ditangkap sewaktu mrk melakukan rondaan.
Translated Text:
last week, a friend of mine was faced with an unfortunate incident involving a corrupt policeman.

his girlfriend (Indonesian) was arrested while MRK was patrolling.

Text:
setelah di dibawa ke balai, mrk telah diberitahu yg mrk perlu membayar wang berjumlah rm3k utk dilepaskan

teman wanitanya pula kerjanya hanya sebagai cleaner, jadi gajinya kecil.
Translated Text:
after being taken to the station, Mrk was told that he had to pay RM3k to be released

his girlfriend only works as a cleaner, so her salary is small.

Text:
jadi rakan saya terpaksa meminjam dari rakan yg lain utk membantu teman wanitanya.

rayuan demi rayuan, akhirnya teman wanitanya dapat dilepaskan selepas membayar rm1.6k

gaji sebulan teman wanitanya hilang begitu saja.
Translated Text:
so my friend had to borrow from another friend to help his girlfriend.

appeal after appeal, finally his girlfriend was released after paying rm1.6k

his girlfriend's monthly salary just disappeared.

Text:
urusan seperti ini pula bukan urusan rasmi.

kadang2 perkara  sepeerti ini sangat merisaukan. 

pihak polis yg sepatutnya menjaga keselamatan org awam tetapi apabila perkara seperti ini terjadi, bagaimana org awam mahu mempercayai pihak polis?
Translated Text:
this kind of business is not an official business.

sometimes things like this are very troubling.

the police who are supposed to take care of the safety of the public but when things like this happen, how can the public trust the police?

Text:
saya sarankan IGP utk segera mewujudkan mekanisma yg komprehensif bagi menangani isu korupsi dalam kalangan pihak polis.

Insitusi polis sewajarnya amanah, berintegriti dan bertanggungjawab!

jangan biarkan individu korup mencemarkan institusi polis!
Translated Text:
I recommend the IGP to immediately establish a comprehensive mechanism to deal with the issue of corruption among the police.

Police institutions should be trustworthy, have integrity and be responsible!

don't let corrupt individuals pollute the police institution!

Text: Chondrosis adalah sebuah penyakit yang mana tulang rawan penghidapnya rosak seiring masa. Penyakitnya sudah masuk ke tahap yang kritikal ketika umurnya 20.
Translated Text: Chondrosis is a disease in which the sufferer's cartilage breaks down over time. His illness had reached a critical stage when he was 20.

Text: Kini, umurnya 37 dan kebanyakan anggota badannya tidak dapat bergerak kecuali jari-jemarinya. Sebelum ini, dia masih boleh berdiri dan merangkak untuk melakukan kerja-kerja seperti mengambil air atau ke tandas.
Translated Text: Now, he is 37 and cannot move most of his limbs except his fingers. Before, he could still stand and crawl to do things like fetch water or go to the toilet.

Text: Dia juga menghidap sakit tulang belakang kerana dia banyak menghabiskan masanya di dalam keadaan duduk dan hanya boleh melakukan sebarang pergerakan apabila sepupu yang menjaganya pulang dari kerja.
Translated Text: He also suffers from back pain because he spends most of his time sitting and can only do any movement when his cousin who takes care of him comes home from work.

Text: Sebelum ini, bapanya menjaga dan membantunya namun semenjak bapanya meninggal pd bulan Jan lepas, dia mengharapkan bantuan dari ibu saudara dan sepupu yang tinggal bersamanya.
Translated Text: Before, his father took care of him and helped him but since his father died last January, he expects help from his aunt and cousin who live with him.

Text: Lebih sedih, dia juga mencatu makanannya sendiri untuk memastikan beratnya tidak bertambah dan dia tidak membebankan ibu saudaranya. Difahamkan juga, ibu saudaranya juga menghidap kanser payudara.
Translated Text: To make matters worse, she also rations her own food to make sure she doesn't gain weight and that she doesn't burden her aunt. It is also understood that his aunt also has breast cancer.

Text: Keadaan rumahnya juga sedikit berantakan. Atap rumahnya bocor dan sekiranya hujan lebat dan banjir, rumahnya akan dimasuki air dan dia terpaksa duduk di dalam kawasan rumahnya dipenuhi air. https://t.co/hBiRX98xWM
Translated Text: His house is also a little messy. The roof of his house leaks and if it rains heavily and floods, his house will be flooded and he has to sit inside his house filled with water. https://t.co/hBiRX98xWM

Text: Walaupun begitu, saudara kita ini sangat celik IT. Buat masa ini, dia sedang menjalankan bisnes atas talian dengan menjual barangan am di FB.
Translated Text: Even so, our brother is very IT literate. Currently, he is running an online business by selling general merchandise on FB.

Text: Dia juga ada memberitahu pihak kami yang dia mahu melakukan apa sahaja kerja, asalkan kerja berkenaan berada di dalam keupayaannya.
Translated Text: He also told us that he wants to do any work, as long as the work is within his ability.

Text: Jadi, pihak saya dan NGO Kantin Muzi telah memulakan dana crowdfunding untuknya. Kami telah menyerahkan rm1000 kepadanya. Bagi mereka yang mahu membantu, kalian boleh salurkan bantuan ke akaun ini: https://t.co/J5snK2kJvD
Translated Text: So, my side and the NGO Kantin Muzi have started a crowdfunding fund for him. We have handed over rm1000 to him. For those who want to help, you can donate to this account: https://t.co/J5snK2kJvD

Text: Harapan crowdfunding ini adalah supaya dia boleh membeli sebuah Hoyer lift yang kosnya mencecah hampir rm10,000. Dengan bantuan hoyer lift ini, dia boleh melakukan lebih banyak perkara dengan sendiri. https://t.co/svUi03gGP0

Text:
Berkuatkuasa semalam, denda yang dikenakan terhadap individu ingkar SOP telah dinaikkan dari RM 1k ke RM10k.

Sudahlah begitu, kadang-kala alasan dan sebab mereka didenda juga tidak munasabah dan yang sering menjadi mangsa denda adalah mereka dari golongan kurang berkemampuan.
Translated Text:
Effective yesterday, the fine imposed on individuals who breach the SOP has been increased from RM 1k to RM10k.

That's it, sometimes the reasons and reasons they are fined are also unreasonable and those who are often the victims of fines are those from the underprivileged.

Text: Kami akan membantu untuk membuat rayuan bagi mengurangkan saman yang diberikan. Keutamaan kami adalah kepada mereka yang yang disaman buat kali pertama dan juga mereka yang dari golongan B40.
Translated Text: We will help to make an appeal to reduce the summons given. Our priority is for those who are sued for the first time and also those from the B40 group.

Text: Semalam, Ketua Polis Negara, Tan Sri Dato' Seri Abdul Hamid Bador juga mengeluarkan kenyataan berkenaan perihal denda ini. Mengikut apa yang dinyatakan oleh beliau, denda diberikan boleh diturunkan sehingga RM50, mengikut budi bicara Pegawai Kesihatan Daerah.
Translated Text: Yesterday, the Chief of Police, Tan Sri Dato' Seri Abdul Hamid Bador also issued a statement regarding this fine. According to what he stated, the fine given can be reduced up to RM50, at the discretion of the District Health Officer.

Text: Selain itu, kalau korang dikenakan denda dan ada pihak-pihak yang cuba menyelesaikan isu denda RM10,000 ini melalui pemberian duit kopi, jangan akur! Terima saman tersebut dan biar kami tolong!
Translated Text: In addition, if you are fined and there are parties trying to solve the RM10,000 fine issue by giving money for coffee, don't give in! Accept the summons and let us help!

Text:
Rakyat juga diingatkan untuk sentiasa mematuhi SOP dan berhati-hati! 

We will never know what would happen to us in any circumstances
Translated Text:
People are also reminded to always follow the SOP and be careful!

We will never know what would happen to us in any circumstances

Text:
bagi mereka yang tinggal di luar kawasan Kepong, hubungi dahulu, ADUN/MP kawasan anda. Cuba minta bantuan mereka.

Jikalau mereka tak dapat bantu atau tidak menyediakan khidmat berkenaan, hubungi kami.
Translated Text:
for those who live outside the Kepong area, contact your area assemblyman/MP first. Try asking them for help.

If they cannot help or do not provide the service, contact us.

Text:
Jadi bagaimana caranya nak mohon? Sekarang ni banyak caranya, antaranya adalah melalui portal: https://t.co/FIEj1TCRLk. 

Melalui portal ini kalian boleh daftar dan kalau pernah mohon, semakan pun boleh buat di sini.
Translated Text:
So how do you apply? Now there are many ways, one of which is through the portal: https://t.co/FIEj1TCRLk.

Through this portal you can register and if you have applied, you can also check here.

Text: Untuk pendaftaran online, seeloknya hadir ke pejabat JKM terdekat dalam tempoh 14 hari selepas daftar untuk penyerahan dokumen - dokumen penting
Translated Text: For online registration, it is best to attend the nearest JKM office within 14 days after registration to submit important documents

Text: Antara dokumen penting yang perlu disediakan adalah seperti: https://t.co/EhIZ3jjDF4
Translated Text: Among the important documents that need to be prepared are: https://t.co/EhIZ3jjDF4

Text: Sekiranya pemohon tidak bekerja atau bekerja sendiri, pemohon hendaklah buat Surat Akuan Sumpah. Boleh buat dengan Pesuruhjaya Sumpah
Translated Text: If the applicant does not work or is self-employed, the applicant must make an Affidavit. Can be done with the Commissioner of Oaths

Text: Seeloknya, pergi terus ke pejabat JKM terdekat, di sana nanti boleh mereka bantu sekiranya ada apa-apa.
Translated Text: Ideally, go directly to the nearest JKM office, there they can help if there is anything.

Text:
Borang juga ada dua jenis, borang JKM 20 dan JKM 18.

JKM18 adalah untuk permohonan baharu

JKM20 adalah untuk kaji semula (renewal)
Translated Text:
There are also two types of forms, JKM 20 and JKM 18 forms.

JKM18 is for new applications

JKM20 is for review (renewal)

Text: Selepas dah beri dokumen-dokumen penting, pihak JKM akan melakukan lawatan ke rumah pemohon sekiranya perlu.
Translated Text: After giving the important documents, the JKM will visit the applicant's home if necessary.

Text: Untuk warga Kepong yang ada masalah dengan pengisian borang JKM, Pusat Khidmat Parlimen Kepong ada menyediakan khidmat bimbingan mengisi borang.
Translated Text: For Kepong citizens who have problems with filling out the JKM form, the Kepong Parliamentary Service Center provides a guidance service for filling out the form.

Text: Bantuan rayuan untuk permohonan yang ditolak juga kami bantu *bergantung sebab permohonan ditolak
Translated Text: We also help with appeals for rejected applications *depending on the reason the application was rejected

Text: prosesnya mungkin sedikit renyah, tapi apabila kita hendak minta bantuan, ini adalah proses yang kita harus lalui. Harap membantu serba sedikit.
Translated Text: the process may be a little crunchy, but when we want to ask for help, this is the process we have to go through. Please help a little bit.

Text: Memanglah informasi berkaitan program vaksinasi kita sudah dijelaskan oleh pihak kerajaan, tapi ini masih belum menjelaskan mengapa proses ini mengambil masa yang lama. Bukankah bila dah isytihar darurat perkara ini boleh diuruskan dengan cepat?
Translated Text: It is true that information related to our vaccination program has been explained by the government, but this still does not explain why this process is taking so long. Isn't it possible that once an emergency has been declared, this matter can be dealt with quickly?

Text: Indonesia dan Singapura dah mulakan program vaksinasi mereka. If we don't want to look at them, fine. If we are to compare, less developed nations such as Bangladesh have also started their vaccination program. I just do not get why ours is taking time.
Translated Text: Indonesia dan Singapura dah mulakan program vaksinasi mereka. If we don't want to look at them, fine. If we are to compare, less developed nations such as Bangladesh have also started their vaccination program. I just do not get why ours is taking time.

Text: Lagipun, mengapa program roll out vaccine ini tidak diketuai oleh Menteri Kesihatan kita? Timbalan menteri sampai 2 tapi kerjanya macam tak nampak. Mengapa menteri lain yang uruskan kerja-kerja ini? Usaha kerajaan sekarang ini nak membantu atau tidak?
Translated Text: After all, why is this vaccine roll out program not led by our Health Minister? The deputy minister arrived at 2 but his work was invisible. Why are other ministers in charge of these works? Is the current government trying to help or not?

Text: Apa lagi alasan PN? Darurat diisytiharkan kononnya untuk elak gemelut politik, nak fokus buat kerja. Tapi semua masih sama, kerja masih lewa! Haprak!
Translated Text: What else is the reason for PN? The state of emergency was declared supposedly to avoid political conflicts, to focus on work. But everything is still the same, work is still lazy! Happy!

Text: Fungsi utama pusat khidmat rakyat adalah membantu menyelesaikan masalah rakyat. Kalau di Kepong, fokus kami adalah menyelesaikan masalah masyarakat di kawasan ini. Masalah org di Kepong juga banyak dan pelbagai, dari kebajikan orang ramai sehinggalah masalah perundangan setempat.
Translated Text: The main function of the public service center is to help solve people's problems. If in Kepong, our focus is to solve community problems in this area. People's problems in Kepong are also many and varied, from public welfare to local legal problems.

Text:
1. Masalah jalan/pokok/longkang/etc 

Masalah yang kerap pejabat saya terima adalah berkaitan jalan rosak, longkang pecah/tersumbat, dan pembuangan sampah haram. Untuk isu macam ni kita akan buat aduan terus kepada DBKL untuk tindakan segera.
Translated Text:
1. Road/tree/gutter/etc problems

Problems that my office often receives are related to damaged roads, broken/clogged drains, and illegal dumping. For this kind of issue, we will make a complaint directly to DBKL for immediate action.

Text:
1. Gambar pertama pasal masalah penggarisan jalan di Metro Prima, Kepong

2. Gambar pokok ni pun di tempat yang sama. Betul betul dekat dengan kawasan pusat khidmat kita https://t.co/wmYgv1THYA
Translated Text:
1. The first picture of the road alignment problem in Metro Prima, Kepong

2. The picture of this tree is also in the same place. Really close to our service center area https://t.co/wmYgv1THYA

Text: Sekiranya mereka sudah lapor isu ini kepada pihak berkuasa, apa yang kita tolong adalah kita bantu dengan proses ‚Äúfollow up‚Äù bagi memastikan isu itu diselesaikan. Penduduk juga boleh lapor masalah-masalah ini kepada kita atau lapor di aplikasi ‚ÄúKLCares".
Translated Text: If they have reported this issue to the authorities, what we help is that we help with the "follow up" process to ensure that the issue is resolved. Residents can also report these problems to us or report them on the "KLCares" application.

Text:
Pengadu ambil gambar, beri butiran seperti nama jalan dan masalah dan hantar saja. Sekiranya masalah tak diselesaikan lagi, pengadu tunjuk kepada kami bukti aduan 
dan kami bantu proses ‚Äúfollow-up‚Äù.
Translated Text:
The complainant takes a picture, gives details such as street name and problem and just sends it. If the problem is still not solved, the complainant shows us the proof of the complaint
and we help the "follow-up" process.

Text: ‚Äúfollow up‚Äù yang kita maksudkan di sini sebagai contohnya adalah pemberian surat permohonan ambil tindakan segera mengecat bonggol di Jalan Jinjang Utama, Kepong. Gambar di bawah contoh aduan dibuat di aplikasi tersebut https://t.co/tssdtKzJg8
Translated Text: The "follow up" that we mean here, for example, is the giving of a letter of request to take immediate action to paint the bumps in Jalan Jinjang Utama, Kepong. The picture below is an example of a complaint made on the application https://t.co/tssdtKzJg8

Text:
2. Permohonan bantuan kerajaan 

Di Kepong, banyak warga emas dan kita faham mereka tak celik IT. Sekarang pula banyak permohonan bantuan seperti BSH, BPN, SMUE semua dibuat secara online. Layout website juga kadang kadang memeningkan, jadi susah utk mereka.
Translated Text:
2. Application for government assistance

In Kepong, there are many elderly people and we understand that they are not IT literate. Now many aid applications such as BSH, BPN, SMUE are all made online. The layout of the website is also sometimes dizzying, so it is difficult for them.

Text: Jadi di pejabat, kita bantu mereka isi borang, jelaskan proses permohonan, semak status bantuan, dan memastikan mereka menyediakan dokumen-dokumen penting untuk permohonan. Bila kita dah jelaskan prosedur, lebih senang untuk mereka mohon apa apa nanti kerana dah tahu caranya
Translated Text: So in the office, we help them fill out the form, explain the application process, check the aid status, and make sure they prepare the important documents for the application. When we have explained the procedure, it is easier for them to apply for anything later because they know how

Text:
3. Bantuan kecemasan 

Kita faham ramai yang memerlukan bantuan. Sumber di parlimen kita juga terhad, jadi kami cuba sehabis baik untuk tolong memberikan bantuan kecemasan kepada mereka yang betul betul memerlukan. Caranya mereka hanya hubungi kami sahaja dan kami cuba bantu.
Translated Text:
3. Emergency assistance

We understand that many people need help. Resources in our parliament are also limited, so we try our best to help provide emergency assistance to those who really need it. The trick is they just contact us and we try to help.

Text: bantuan pula dalam pelbagai bentuk. kadang kala dalam bentuk kewangan, dalam bentuk barangan dapur seperti beras dan minyak, barangan rumah, dan lain lain lagi. Tapi sekarang dalam waktu pendemik, antara benda yg kami selalu beri org ramai adalah mask percuma. https://t.co/0Gul2IGM3m
Translated Text: help in various forms. sometimes in the form of money, in the form of kitchen items such as rice and oil, household items, and so on. But now in the pandemic, one of the things we always give people is a free mask. https://t.co/0Gul2IGM3m

Text:
4. Bantuan menulis wasiat bagi golongan tak berkemampuan 

Ramai tak tahu kita buat khidmat ni, sebenarnya ini perkara penting, lebih lebih lagi di hari tua nanti. Tapi sedihnya tak ramai yang mampu nak tulis wasiat. Cajnya mahal juga kalau diikutkan.
Translated Text:
4. Help writing a will for the indigent

Many people don't know that we do this service, actually this is an important thing, even more so in old age. But sadly not many are able to write a will. The charge is also expensive if you follow.

Text: Mujur di pejabat kita, ada sukarelawan dengan background perundangan yang boleh bantu mereka menulis wasiat secara percuma. Tapi perkhidmatan ini tak dibuat selalu dan kalau ingin buat, kena beritahu dulu pejabat kami dulu supaya kami boleh aturkan tarikh. https://t.co/Zq3hq7PO9w
Translated Text: Fortunately, in our office, there are volunteers with a legal background who can help them write a will for free. But this service is not always done and if you want to do it, you have to tell our office first so that we can arrange a date. https://t.co/Zq3hq7PO9w

Text:
5. Nasihat guaman percuma 

Pejabat parlimen kita ada banyak terima sukarela dari sektor perundangan. Jadi mereka boleh serba sedikit membantu org di kawasan kita yg berhadapan dengan masalah undang undang. Jika orang hubungi kita berkaitan masalah ini -
Translated Text:
5. Free legal advice

Our parliamentary office has many volunteers from the legal sector. So they can help people in our area who are dealing with legal problems. If people contact us regarding this problem -

Text: Perlu ditekankan juga di sini, nasihat guaman (legal advice), walaupun percuma, kita akan beri kepada mereka yang betul betul memerlukan sahaja. Contoh masalah undang undang yang kami bantu adalah isu pembahagian harta pusaka.
Translated Text: It should also be emphasized here, legal advice, although free, we will only give it to those who really need it. An example of a legal problem that we help with is the issue of division of inheritance.

Text:
6. Kami juga banyak terima masalah berkaitan hutang dengan geng ah long. Cara kita bantu adalah berunding dengan mereka. Tujuannya adalah supaya kita boleh cari 'middle ground' utk kes-kes sebegini.

p/s: bukanlah rundingan bersama ahlong tetapi interview berkaitan kes ini https://t.co/RUQcNtOnYN
Translated Text:
6. We also receive a lot of debt-related problems with the ah long gang. The way we help is to consult with them. The purpose is so that we can find a 'middle ground' for such cases.

p/s: not a negotiation with ahlong but an interview related to this case https://t.co/RUQcNtOnYN

Text: 7. Ada juga kadang kadang kita terima, masalah dari luar dari kawasan parlimen, contohnya Batu, Seputeh, Pulau Pinang pun ada! Walaupun ini diluar kawasan parlimen, kita akan lanjutkan isu mereka ini kepada rakan rakan kita di kawasan parlimen tersebut :)
Translated Text: 7. There are also sometimes we accept, problems from outside the parliamentary area, for example Batu, Seputeh, Penang there are also! Although this is outside the parliamentary area, we will continue their issue to our friends in the parliamentary area :)

Text: Jadi itulah antara kerja-kerja yg pejabat parlimen saya lakukan sekarang ini. kalau korang orang kepong dan ada cadangan utk beri kepada kami, bolehlah hubungi kami di hotline kami! Kami cuba yang terbaik untuk korang!
Translated Text: So that is one of the works that my parliamentary office is doing right now. If you are a kepong person and have a suggestion to give us, you can contact us on our hotline! We try our best for you!

Text: kalau nak collaborate untuk program kebajikan ke ke nak bagi sumbangan ke, itu pun tiada masalah. Wasep-wasep je kita akan respond!
Translated Text: if you want to collaborate for welfare programs or if you want to donate, that's no problem either. We'll respond just by sending a message!
